Haversine Formula
What is Haversine?

The Haversine Formula is used to calculate the shortest distance between two points on the surface of a sphere (Earth) using their:

Latitude
Longitude

This distance is called the great-circle distance.

Earth is not flat, so:

Straight-line (Euclidean) distance → inaccurate for large distances
Haversine → considers Earth’s curvature

